ch, people's interpretations of Catholicism, and representations of Jewish communities in Mexico—allows the films to critically engage with Mexican politics, identity, and social issues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszMexico. 0aMotion pictureszMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszMexicoxHistoryy21st century. 0aReligion in motion pictures. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848532440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485324423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485324/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles